SIGNIO v. UNITED STATES. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 20, 1923.) No. 162. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Eastern District of New York. Angelo Signio was convicted of the unlawful sale of liquor, and he brings error. Affirmed. Thomas O’Rourke Gallagher, for plaintiff in error. Ralph Greene, U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Henry Walsh, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y., of counsel), for the United States.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and MANTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in open court.
